medical_history.chief_complaint: Familial multiple lipomatosis, requiring removal of multiple lipomas.
medical_history.history_of_present_illness: Symptoms of multiple encapsulated lipomas present; patient likely diagnosed in the third decade of life. Tumors are discrete and mobile, distributed over arms, thighs, and trunk.
medical_history.past_medical_history: Diagnosis of familial multiple lipomatosis based on patient and family history, physical examination, and previous excision.
medical_history.family_history: Family members have similar condition (familial multiple lipomatosis).
